Comey reveals that Trump's associates are under a counterintelligence investigation for ties to Russia while Trump rants about it on twitter. That and subsequent revelations are said to put a "big gray cloud" over the Trump administration. Trump continues to insist Obama spied on him. Meanwhile, Trump's associates are stiffing NATO and blocking Sally Yate's testimony on Flynn. Biden wonders "what the hell are we doing." Schiff insists there is evidence of cover-ups and collusion and Grassley raises a stink about FBI connections with the "dirty dossier."

The Washington Post reports that Trump tried to block Sally Yates from testifying, adding another "big gray cloud" to the "storm" of Russian collusion over Trump's presidency. Trump complains the media is treating him unfairly. Republicans vote to block Congress from obtaining Trump's tax returns, and the next day Lavrov mentions that it's "still possible" for Trump "renew cooperation" in fighting terrorism in Syria, saying "We will be sharing this approach, I am sure." Trump doubles down on allowing Assad to stay put.

Meanwhile, Comey mentions that he "knows when he's going to cause a storm" but he "doesn't care." On the morning of March 30th, Flynn offers to testify for the Russia probe in exchange for immunity. That same morning, Trump calls Comey.

Trump says he has nothing to do with Russia, and "the cloud" of the Russia investigation is impairing his dealmaking abilities. He asks Comey what they could do to "lift the cloud." Trump and Comey agree that the FBI should do the investigation well, but Trump reemphasizes that "the cloud" is causing him problems.

Reading between the lines of Comey's statement, it looks like Trump asks Comey why he publicly confirmed the counterintelligence investigation into his associates, and Comey tells him that Congress wanted it. 
This call is said to be the third time Comey tells Trump he is not under investigation. Trump repeatedly tells Comey "we need get it out" that he is not under investigation, and says it would be good to clear the names of his associates if they haven't done anything wrong. 

In an apparent attempt to bargain, Trump points out to Comey that he hadn't mentioned "the McCabe thing" (that McCabe had the appearance of a conflict of interest regarding donations from Clinton associates) since Comey said McMabe is "honorable." Comey repeats that McCabe is "honorable" and Trump reiterates that the "cloud" is hurting his dealmaking and he wants the public to know he's not under investigation. Comey tells him "I'll see what we can do."

After the meeting, a journalist claims to have found Comey's twitter account, which is following several high-profile journalists who have been reporting on the Russia story in the Washington Post and New York Times. Trump tweets that Flynn should ask for immunity but maintains that the Russia investigation is a "witch hunt" and an "excuse" by the media and Democrats.

Trump continues to tweet that the Russia investigation is made up and that Obama intelligence officials are out to get him.


