https://twitter.com/realdonaldtrump/status/852510810287075329
	Things will work out fine between the U.S.A. and Russia. At the right time everyone will come to their senses & there will be lasting peace!
	6:16 AM - 13 Apr 2017 


The cloud of Russian collusion over Trump's presidency lingers. Assad attacks his own people in one of the worst chemical attacks in years. Russian involvement is suspected. Putin posits that 95% of the worlds terrorist attacks are orchestrated by the CIA.

Putin signals less than enthusiastic support for Assad. Trump orders a cruise missile strike on a Syrian airfield over dinner with Chinese President Xi. Trump seems to think this makes him very cool. The strike is largely symbolic, although Mattis will later claim it destroyed "40% of Syria's air force."

Russia warns of "serious consequences" for the missile strike. Protestors around the country demand Trump to release his tax returns, and larger protests are planned for next week. Trump's administration can't make up its mind on whether or not it supports Assad.

U.S. intelligence finds Russian foreknowledge of the chemical strike and evidence of a cover up. The Trump administration disputes this. Trump remains silent on his Syria policy. Putin refuses to meet Tillerson at his next visit to Moscow.

The next day, Trump calls up Comey again to ask him his request to "get it out" that he is not under investigation. Comey tells Trump he forwarded his request to Boente but hasn't heard back. Trump tells Comey that "the cloud" was getting in the way of his ability to do his job, and says he might have "his people" reach out to Boente. Comey says this is what Trump should do. Trump says he will, and adds "Because I have been very loyal to you, very loyal; we had that thing you know." Trump ends the call saying he will reach out to Boente. That was the last time Comey spoke to Trump.

The next day, the Washington post leaks that Trump advisor Carter Page is under investigation for acting as an agent of Russian intelligence. Trump posits that maybe it's possible that Russia had foreknowledge of the Syria attack. Putin charges that U.S. relations have gotten worse under Trump. Trump tweets that "things will work out fine between the U.S.A and Russia."


